  "title": "R&D Platform Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>Operate and maintain <strong>test platforms</strong> and support controlled chemical/electrochemical experiments.\nAssemble and troubleshoot <strong>mechanical, fluidic, and electrical </strong>subsystems, perform calibrations, and keep meticulous records.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Set up and run experiments; monitor system/environmental conditions; record accurate data.</li><li>Collect samples and perform basic analyses (pH, conductivity, titrations).</li><li>Assemble/troubleshoot/maintain pumps, piping, sensors, wiring, PLCs; perform periodic <strong>calibration</strong>.</li><li>Maintain safety, cleanliness, and readiness of work areas; adhere to SOPs and EHS protocols.</li><li>Support new prototype installs; assist engineers with test improvements and documentation.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>ITE/Diploma in Mechanical/Chemical/Electrical or related.</li><li>1–4+ years operating lab/pilot test rigs or production test systems.</li><li>Hands‑on with tools, fittings, sensors; disciplined documentation habit.</li></ul>",
